name: Indira Gandhi National Old Age Pension Scheme (IGNOAPS)
description: Provides monthly pension to senior citizens from Below Poverty Line households.

name: Atal Pension Yojana (APY)
description: A pension scheme focused on workers in the unorganized sector offering defined pension after 60.

name: Varishtha Pension Bima Yojana
description: Provides assured pension with a return of 8% to senior citizens for 10 years.

name: Senior Citizen Health Insurance Scheme (SCHIS)
description: Offers additional health cover to senior citizens already enrolled in RSBY.

name: National Programme for the Health Care of the Elderly (NPHCE)
description: Dedicated healthcare services to the elderly at primary, secondary, and tertiary levels.

name: Rashtriya Vayoshri Yojana (RVY)
description: Provides assistive devices to senior citizens belonging to BPL category with age-related disabilities.

name: Annapurna Scheme
description: Provides 10 kg of free food grain per month to senior citizens not covered under IGNOAPS.

name: Maintenance and Welfare of Parents and Senior Citizens Act
description: Legal protection ensuring children or heirs maintain elderly parents or pay maintenance.

name: Travel Concessions for Senior Citizens
description: Railways and various airlines offer fare discounts for senior citizens.

name: SAMPARK: Senior Citizen Helpline (14567)
description: A national helpline offering assistance in legal, health, emotional, and abuse-related issues.

name: Support to Training and Employment Programme for Women (STEP)
description: Provides training and skills to single and marginalized women to become self-employed.

name: One Stop Centre Scheme (Sakhi)
description: Supports single and distressed women facing violence with shelter, legal, and psychological help.

name: Swadhar Greh Scheme
description: Provides shelter and support for women in difficult circumstances including deserted and single women.

name: Indira Gandhi National Widow Pension Scheme (IGNWPS)
description: Monthly pension for widows aged 40–59 living below the poverty line.

name: Working Women Hostel Scheme
description: Provides safe and affordable accommodation to working and single women.

name: Mahila Samakhya Programme
description: Promotes empowerment and education among socially disadvantaged women.

name: Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY) – Women Ownership Priority
description: Gives preference to single women as beneficiaries for subsidized home ownership.

name: Mukhya Mantri Kanya Vivah Yojana (State-specific)
description: Financial assistance to single poor women at the time of marriage.

name: Ujjawala Scheme
description: Rehabilitation and reintegration of trafficked women including shelter and vocational training.

name: Kishori Shakti Yojana
description: Empowers adolescent girls through nutrition, education, and life skills.

name: Beti Bachao Beti Padhao (BBBP)
description: Aimed at ensuring survival, protection, and education of the girl child.

name: Pradhan Mantri Mahila Shakti Kendra
description: Focuses on empowering women through community engagement, local leadership, and skill training.

name: Pradhan Mantri Mudra Yojana (PMMY)
description: Provides easy access to credit for small business owners, especially women entrepreneurs.

name: Nari Shakti Puraskar
description: National awards to women who have made exceptional contributions to society.

name: PM Jan Dhan Yojana (Women)
description: Financial inclusion scheme for women, offering bank accounts with zero balance.

name: PMAY - Women Ownership
description: Priority housing benefits for women, under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana.

name: Mahila E-Haat
description: Online platform for women entrepreneurs to sell products and services.

name: National Creche Scheme
description: Provides crèche facilities to working women for their children under 6 years.

name: Self-Help Group (SHG) Programme
description: Supports women through group-based savings and income-generating activities.

name: National Women's Commission (NWC)
description: A statutory body for addressing issues related to women's rights and welfare.

name: Women & Child Development Scheme (WCD)
description: Various schemes for the welfare of women and children, including health and education.

name: Swachh Bharat Mission (Gramin) – Women
description: Focuses on providing toilet facilities for rural women.

name: Women Entrepreneurship Platform
description: An initiative to support women entrepreneurs with access to services and financial resources.

name: Mission Indradhanush (Women)
description: Aimed at improving immunization coverage in women and children.

name: Pradhan Mantri Kaushal Vikas Yojana (PMKVY) - Women
description: Skills development initiative for women to enhance employability.

name: Ujjwala Yojana
description: Provides LPG connections to poor women from Below Poverty Line households.

name: Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY)
description: Affordable housing scheme for rural and urban poor.

name: PMAY – Urban
description: Subsidized housing for the urban poor, with preference to women and marginalized communities.

name: PMAY – Rural
description: Scheme for affordable housing specifically targeting rural areas.

name: Fisheries and Aquaculture Infrastructure Development Fund (FIDF)
description: Provides financial assistance for the development of the fisheries and aquaculture sector.

name: Kisan Credit Card Scheme (KCC)
description: Helps farmers access easy credit for purchasing agricultural inputs.

name: Pradhan Mantri Fasal Bima Yojana (PMFBY)
description: Crop insurance scheme to protect farmers from natural calamities and yield loss.

name: Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Act (MGNREGA)
description: Provides 100 days of wage employment per year to rural households.

name: National Social Assistance Programme (NSAP)
description: Provides social assistance to poor families, including pensions and other welfare schemes.

name: Swachh Bharat Abhiyan
description: A nationwide cleanliness campaign to ensure a clean and sanitary environment for all.

name: National Handloom Development Programme (NHDP)
description: Promotes and develops handloom products and handloom weavers.

name: National Rural Livelihood Mission (NRLM)
description: Improves the livelihood of rural people, particularly women, through self-employment.

name: Skill Development Initiative Scheme (SDIS)
description: Provides training to youth and adults in various sectors to enhance their employability.

name: Pradhan Mantri Kaushal Vikas Yojana (PMKVY)
description: Aims to provide industry-relevant skill training to youth for employment and entrepreneurship.

name: National Urban Livelihood Mission (NULM)
description: Improves urban livelihoods through self-employment and skill development programs.

name: Deen Dayal Upadhyaya Grameen Kaushalya Yojana (DDU-GKY)
description: A skill development program targeting youth from rural areas.

name: Atal Mission for Rejuvenation and Urban Transformation (AMRUT)
description: Improves urban infrastructure and ensures water supply, sewerage, and green spaces.

name: Swadesh Darshan Scheme
description: Promotes tourism by developing infrastructure in key tourist circuits across India.

name: Beti Bachao Beti Padhao
description: Aims to generate awareness and improve the efficiency of welfare services for girls.

name: Balika Samriddhi Yojana
description: Provides financial assistance to girls from BPL families to encourage education and delay marriage.

name: Ladli Scheme (State-specific)
description: Encourages the birth and education of girl children with financial incentives.

name: Sukanya Samriddhi Yojana
description: Savings scheme for the education and marriage of the girl child.

name: National Child Labour Project (NCLP)
description: Provides education, vocational training, and rehabilitation to children rescued from child labour.

name: Integrated Child Protection Scheme (ICPS)
description: Ensures safety and welfare of children in difficult circumstances including those in need of care and protection.

name: Childline 1098
description: 24x7 helpline for children in distress offering emergency support, rescue, and aid.

name: National Scholarship Portal (NSP) – Central Sector Scheme
description: Scholarships for meritorious students from economically weaker sections pursuing college and university education.

name: Post Matric Scholarship for SC/ST/OBC Students
description: Financial aid for SC, ST, and OBC students studying in post-secondary or higher education.

name: National Means-cum-Merit Scholarship Scheme (NMMSS)
description: Encourages economically weaker students to continue studies at secondary and higher secondary levels.

name: Prime Minister’s Scholarship Scheme for Central Armed Police Forces and Assam Rifles
description: Scholarships for wards and widows of CAPF & AR personnel pursuing professional courses.

name: Vidya Lakshmi Education Loan Scheme
description: Provides a single window platform for students to apply for education loans from multiple banks.

name: Startup India
description: A flagship initiative to support startups with benefits like tax exemption, funding, incubation, and simplified regulations.

name: Stand-Up India
description: Provides bank loans between ₹10 lakh to ₹1 crore to SC/ST and women entrepreneurs to start a business.

name: MUDRA Yojana
description: Provides micro-financing under Shishu, Kishore, and Tarun categories for small and micro-businesses.

name: Prime Minister’s Employment Generation Programme (PMEGP)
description: Credit-linked subsidy for setting up new micro-enterprises in the non-farm sector.

name: ASPIRE Scheme
description: Promotes rural entrepreneurship through incubation and funding support to agro-based startups and microenterprises.

name: PM Vishwakarma Yojana
description: Provides recognition, skill training, toolkits, and credit support to traditional artisans and craftsmen (like carpenters, blacksmiths, potters).

name: PM Gati Shakti Yojana
description: National Master Plan for multi-modal connectivity to reduce logistics cost and time across sectors.

name: PM e-Vidya
description: A digital education initiative that integrates all digital learning platforms including DIKSHA, SWAYAM, and TV channels for school and higher education.

name: Agri Infra Fund
description: Aims to provide medium-long term debt financing for investments in viable agriculture infrastructure projects.

name: National Digital Health Mission (Ayushman Bharat Digital Mission)
description: Provides every citizen with a digital health ID and centralized access to their health records securely.

name: Mera Yuva Bharat (MY Bharat)
description: A platform to engage youth in nation-building through volunteering, internships, and leadership programs.

name: PM Kisan Samman Nidhi
description: Provides ₹6,000 annual income support to all small and marginal farmers in three equal installments.

name: Digital India Bhashini
description: Aims to make digital services and the internet accessible in Indian languages using AI-powered translation tools.

name: Startup India Seed Fund Scheme (SISFS)
description: Provides financial assistance to startups for proof of concept, prototype development, and product trials.

name: e-Shram Portal
description: National database for unorganized workers for delivery of social security schemes and benefits.
